ug\": \"neo4j\",\n      \"reason\": \"The official driver documentation's primary example connects to bolt://localhost:7687 and runs Cypher; a Neo4j server is needed to cover Driver, Session, connectivity verification, and query execution paths.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For server-backed tests, start a local Neo4j container in test setup, configure `NEO4J_AUTH=neo4j/testpassword`, map Bolt port `7687`, connect with `GraphDatabase.driver(\\\"bolt://localhost:7687\\\", AuthTokens.basic(\\\"neo4j\\\", \\\"testpassword\\\"))`, wait until `driver.verifyConnectivity()` succeeds before running queries, and stop the process/container in teardown. Keep client-side mapping/value tests as they do not require server setup.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The current reported failure is in client-side object mapping, so Docker is not required to reproduce that exact failing test.\",\n    \"Neo4j startup can take several seconds; tests must poll for connectivity instead of assuming the port is ready immediately.\",\n    \"A fixed host port such as 7687 can conflict with a locally running Neo4j instance during local verification.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06e1e543a0760db0016a41f3270720819382747dd556510312\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1338, "output": 1941, "cacheRead": 39424, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42703, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782706960107, "responseId": "resp_06e1e543a0760db0016a41f310b86881939d8d8acd4d7a5bc2"}}
